  <p>
      <b>Notes</b>
:
  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_postcode">POSTCODE</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_postcode">POSTCODE</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
For further information on 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_postcode">POSTCODES</xref>
, see:  </p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/nhs_postcode_directory.asp"
                  scope="external"
                  format="html">NHS_Postcode_Directory</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/contact_details.asp"
                  scope="external"
                  format="html">Contact_Details</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/methodology/geography/ukgeographies/postalgeography"
                  scope="external"
                  format="html">Office for National Statistics website: Postal geography</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_nhs_digital">NHS Digital</xref>
            <p>
 website at: 
                <xref href="https://digital.nhs.uk/organisation-data-service/data-downloads/postcode-files"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">ODS postcode files</xref>
.        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
If a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_postcode">POSTCODE</xref>
 is not known, (for example, the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 has no fixed abode, the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 is an 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_overseas_visitor">Overseas Visitor</xref>
 etc.) the appropriate 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/organisation_data_service.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Organisation_Data_Service</xref>
 pseudo 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_postcode">POSTCODE</xref>
 should be used.  </p>
  <p>
The pseudo 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_postcode">POSTCODES</xref>
 can be found on the 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/organisation_data_service.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Organisation_Data_Service</xref>
 pages of the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nhs_digital">NHS Digital</xref>
 website at: 
    <xref href="https://digital.nhs.uk/services/organisation-data-service/data-downloads/office-for-national-statistics-data"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Office for National Statistics data</xref>
.  </p>


